Anterior nare pierced in front side of a pointed flap-like tube, tip reaching at least anterior margin of eye. Posterior nare adjacent to anterior one. Mouth arched, gape about 2–2.5 times wider than long (
Fig. 11
). Lips fleshy. Upper lip with median notch, with a few shallow wrinkles. Processus dentiformis present. Lower lip with wide median interruption; median part smooth, with 1–3 sulci, lateral part smooth or with small wrinkles. Tip of lower jaw not exposed.A median concavity in lower jaw. Inner rostral barbel reaching corner of mouth; outer one reaching vertical of middle of eye. Maxillary barbel reaching beyond middle of postorbital area.

Intestine with a loop behind stomach (
Fig. 12a
). Air bladder without posterior chamber in abdominal cavity. Two halves of bony capsule of anterior chamber of air bladder connected by a manubrium (
Fig. 12b
).

